CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1959, pg. 6, reads: "'Y' Volunteers Honored - Centre Avenue Branch YMCA Volunteer Club leaders were honored at a recognition dinner there, recently. Among them were, seated, left to right Mrs. Agnes Dickson, Miss Bettie Webster, Harry Singer, chairman of the youth committee; Mrs. Erma P. Williams and Mrs. Lucille Wooden. Second row: John Brewer, guest speaker and chairman of the leadership recruitment committee; Atty. Byrd R. Brown, chairman of the branch board of management, Charles Biggs, Robert Phillips, Jodie West and Ronald Curry. Third row: Conley Davies, Metropolitan youth secretary; William Cook, Robert Lee Edwards Jr., physical director, and Paul Dykes, youth secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Centre Avenue Branch YMCA Volunteer Club Leaders, seated from left: Agnes Dickson, Bettie Webster, Harry Singer, Erma P.
